header.gameNote: PARADISE JAM AT ST JOHN VIRGIN ISLANDS

article.headline: Old Dominion 65, Fordham 52
article.story: CHARLOTTE AMALIE, U.S. Virgin Islands (AP) -- Alex Loughton had 17 points, 15 rebounds and three blocked shots to lead Old Dominion to a 65-52 victory over Fordham at the Paradise Jam tournament on Saturday night. Drew Williamson scored 15 points for Old Dominion, which plays in the championship game Monday against either Wisconsin or Eastern Kentucky. Bryant Dunston had 18 points and 14 rebounds for Fordham, which plays Georgia on Sunday, in the six-team round-robin tournament. Fordham lead the entire first half, but the Monarchs rallied to tie the score at 29 early in the second half. The lead changed nine times before timely 3-pointers by Williamson and Isaiah Hunter gave Old Dominion a nine-point lead with 2:03 to play.
